                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>EdgarRamza wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Oh my... something something.
<br />

<br />
Each enchanter has his own style, but I STRONGLY recommend getting mobs down evenly and then invis'ing + nuking them both down.
<br />

<br />
For starters, you don't have a 33% exp penalty and don't need to burn mana with slow/haste. 
<br />

<br />
Second, you will be , in essence, killing 2 mobs at once, for less mana, faster then you kill 2 with the haste/slow method.
<br />

<br />
If your ex-pet reaches you, there is also a smaller risk of death, since its not hasted....
<br />

<br />
Oh well, to each his own.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I agree.  Pacy one. Pull the other with tash and run.  When gems appear, root your soon to be pet.  Charm him and make him guard.  Pull the other with a Blue band just incase pet kills before you can get your invis off.  Run through pet and make him attack.  When the pulled mob comes near the pet, he'll forget about you as the pet starts to beat his head in.
<br />

<br />
Go off aways and med some.  Keep that trigger finger on root.  Drop pacy for a nuke.  Keep an eye on your pet's and the mobs hps.  I can usually nuke for around 5% of their hps.  I wait until either the pet is around 15% or the mob is, then run back a few more steps and self invis.  Usually, I have 2 mobs here standing side by side rooted, with 3-10% hp.  
<br />

<br />
When I kill them this way, I usually get 5-6% AA per kill.  
<br />

<br />
The plus side to this is:
<br />
1) Charm breaks rarely happen with the tashed mob (and TD 2)
<br />
2) Pets are temporary, so see advantage #1
<br />
3) Get full exp for both kills.  10% per 2 is really nice for me (non uber gear)
<br />
4) I can go med, AFK or whatever anytime within a 2 kill time period without worrying about charm breaking while afk or anything.  It's nice to med in peace.
<br />

<br />
When working in the rooms with 3...
<br />

<br />
Pull one with tash. Run and root when able.
<br />
Charm new pet.
<br />
Pull a mob with a BCB.
<br />
Tash and root when next to pet.
<br />
Slow this mob down.  This pet need to live through 2 fights.
<br />
When mob almost dead, cast invis.  Nuke the mob.  Re-charm pet.
<br />
Pull other mob and slow.  If you time things right, both should be low on HP about the same time.
<br />

<br />
Ways to make pet take more damage:
<br />
1)Tell him to guard and then keep backing off.  The other mob will get in a few more hits without taking them this way.
<br />
2) Open for more ideas???
<br />

<br />
Ways to hurt the mob more if pet is losing.
<br />
1) Put a small slow on mob if odds are really really bad.
<br />
2) NDT on pet for extra dmg and healing self (however, with hits in the 544s, this prolly won't matter a lot)
<br />
3) Nuke mob
<br />
4) Smack the mob with a dot that drops ac and agi.  Costs more mana than nuke, but over time can help pet even the odds some.
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is my favorite way to solo this place since I tend to need to go afk or have "safer" med breaks sometimes.  
<br />

<br />
Just my 2 cents.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
