                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">When working in the rooms with 3...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I used to prefer hasting the pet, not slowing the first mob, and only slowing the second if pet was at 15pc (slow would land at about 10pc, sometimes lower). Its better imo because its faster which means your pet's root has less chance of breaking before it expires. 
<br />

<br />
These days I leave the two guards and pet one to kill the one in the other area for full xp again as the last pair of the shrine. That normally gives me a couple of minutes to med up before the entrance mobs pop again.
<br />

<br />
If there's a named I would haste my pet taken from just outside the room and use him to kill his partner and one from the room, then use fresh pet on named. Remember they can be blissed (the named) so you can get max xp from them too if you're careful.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
