                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Izzuyen,
<br />

<br />
I'm in such a state of conflict over your guide to HoH here.  A conflict which stems from the fact that in 3 weeks, I've managed to earn close to half the AA's  my paladin earned over the course of just under 2 years.
<br />

<br />
But that aside... THANK YOU!!! and DAMN YOU!!!
<br />

<br />
I'm having a serious crisis of faith right now because ever since I decided to give this a go - I have a hard time logging on my paladin and slogging through 2-4hr AA nights (no access to EP yet).  I'm hoping that once I get just a "few" more of the essential AA's (you know, mc3,gm,scs,qb2,pi,er3,ca3,cs3,lr5,id5 :)) I can get back to my paladin... But in the meantime, I just wanted to share some of my experiences charm soloing in HoH.
<br />

<br />
When I started out - I had just about 3.7k 4k mana, FT1, 4 AA's, a bunch of sow potions and a bad attitude.  3 weeks later I have, 40 AA's, and an almost completely overhauled rig consisting of an ER4 item, spell haste, mana pres4,improved dam4.  Still have FT1 and a bad attitude but I'm working on fixing those last 2.
<br />

<br />
AA's bought in order
<br />
run3
<br />
TD3 (do not regret this early purchase one bit)
<br />
metabo3 (nor this)
<br />
scm3 (nor this)
<br />
er1 (iffy on this)
<br />
8 banked - waiting for lunch time to go getlast one for MGB
<br />

<br />
Of the aa's above - I can't stress how much I've enjoyed buying TD3 and SCM3 - I even changed my specialization once I realized how much mana I was using constantly buffing.  In the year or so I've had this chanter - he barely hit 140 specialization in conjuration(for mez)  - and in 3 weeks of charm soloing and raiding - he's already hit 160 in alteration and climbing fast.  The combination of those 3 choices plus the focus effect items allow me to tear through HoH/SS at full speed.   Because my FT is severely lacking - I can't go with the nuke both down method - so I've been working at perfecting the charm/haste/slow method.  When you said in your original post "Death will be rare" you weren't kidding - taking the necessary precautions and being on the ball make it extremely hard to die.
<br />

<br />
So here's some notes:
<br />

<br />
Breaking pairs
<br />
- Pacify target, tash pet, run, charm, haste, sic pet, tash target, slow, CBB, root
<br />
- the last key stroke is F1 to target pet and stay targeted.  Run a safe distance away (just out of ER4 casting range)  and if charm breaks (which it will at the worst possible moment) - all you need to do is pull the trigger and recharm.  The target should be rooted by this point - so all you have to do is recharm the pet and send it in again.
<br />
- After that - it's a simple matter of guarding your pet, pacifying pairs and proximity pulling your next target.  
<br />

<br />
Positioning your pet
<br />
- I always guard the pet at the end of a hallway in line of sight where possible - then drag the target to the pet.  I do this to give myself enough room to be just out of ER4 casting range so if charm breaks, I can recharm the pet without taking a single step.  
<br />
- When breaking charm and grabbing new pet - remember you have to give yourself room to tash - run a little - then charm again without running into your ex pet.  So root the ex pet well enough away.  I usually park him in a corner - run to the intersection break mez - then root right away.  
<br />

<br />
I've had a couple of close calls where sow dropped and I was standing just outside of melee range of rooted ex pet - with *barely* enough distance to recharm pet.  His fist was about a millimeter from my face when charm landed and he said "oops hehe just kidding master".
<br />

<br />
Breaking charm
<br />
I have 2 choices - I either:
<br />
a) root/nuke the ex pet down, or 
<br />
b) root it and send a new pet at him.
<br />

<br />
Option a
<br />
- target pet - run a safe distance away - cast improved invis and root pet once in range - root and nuke to your heart's content.  
<br />

<br />
Option b
<br />
- recant magic to dispell buffs, root ex-pet, charm/buff a new one, cbb ex pet, re root if necessary - sic pet.  I CBB before sending in new pet because even at 20% - the ex pet might be alive for just a hair under 10-15 seconds.  There's no need to debuff him plus I can't tell you how many times I've forgotten to plink him with the dot and getting ks'd by my pet.
<br />

<br />
I figure - charm and haste is 1000 mana. Nuke's from 15% with an ID4 focus item may or may not take 3 nukes (900 mana).  It may yield more xp per kill - but over time I lose a LOT of time medding because of my lack of FT.  When I hit FT7 this should no longer be an issue, but for now - it's more mana efficient to charm a new pet rather than nuke one down (although I'll admit it's fun as hell).
<br />

<br />
Named
<br />
I hate those guys - charm almost ALWAYS seems to break during these fights.  For that reason alone - I keep the named mobs targeted after debuffs have been applied and have my mez trigger finger ready to go.  Since they run than the guardians, if you don't have ample running room (i.e. both rooms cleared) you're going to have a beast of a time getting your pet to hit him.  In some cases - if I don't have ample running room - I'll simply mez both and camp out - overall it's faster to recharm and have at it again - than to risk dieing or getting jumped by respawns.
<br />

<br />
The rewards
<br />
again 3 weeks later 40 aa's 
<br />
A new rig almost completely funded by selling spells from parchment turn ins
<br />
40 stacks of Hero Parts which will go into baking and more cash (sell for 100pp-150pp per on my server)
<br />

<br />
I still have a lot to learn as an enchanter - but it's all starting to make sense :)  I was charm duoing in PoN helping a friend level his mage. Although the surroundings were different - the strategies were the same - between the 2 of us - we were able to clear the entire wolf camp and anything that happened to wander too close to our camp all done without a single death.  Once I get flagged for Tactics - I'll see if I can hit one of those 20 min aa marks :) but for now - I'm about as content as I can be.
<br />

<br />
So again - Izzuyen - my paladin's not too fond of you right now - but my chanter thanks you :)
<br />

<br />
Cheers</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=189883" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Ephemeral Bliss</span></a>
