                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">All damage is good damage:
<br />

<br />
Charm 1 mob.  Haste it (clicky haste saves a spell slot).
<br />

<br />
Pull another mob, BCB it.  Have them fight.
<br />

<br />
Chain pull mobs.  Break charm when pet is lowish.  All damage is good damage -- don't slow NPC's.
<br />

<br />
If you have two mobs that have low hps, break charm, and nuke both down.  Otherwise don't bother.  If you are feeling your oats, break charm on your pet, nuke down non-pet, pull another mob, and use other mob as new pet.  With practice you can do this with basically zero downtime (have 2nd mob inc, clicky break charm, charm new mob, new mob /pet attacks old pet, BCB old pet, nuke mob pet was attacking, haste new pet).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
